abstract: The Toronto-Dominion Bank said Thursday its profit rose 19 percent in the second quarter, helped by a strong performance in all business lines except its retail banking in the United States. Toronto Dominion said it earned 879 million Canadian dollars ($814 million), or 1.20 Canadian dollars a share, up from 738 million Canadian dollars, or 1.01 Canadian dollars a share, a year earlier.
